Currently only testing Linux, but support for other platforms will be added.

Why use cmake?  Because different platforms may need special linker flags in
order to access the process table.  PGXS didn't have a way to modify the
LDFLAGS when the MODULES directive is used.

Install
-------
make
make install
psql -f pg_proctab.sql
psql -f pg_loadavg.sql
psql -f pg_cputime.sql
psql -f pg_memusage.sql

Uninstall
---------

xargs rm < install_manifest.txt

Examples
--------
SELECT procpid
FROM pg_stat_activity;

SELECT *
FROM pg_proctab();

SELECT *
FROM pg_stat_activity, pg_proctab()
WHERE procpid = pid;
